==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Queen olive
<hw>Queen olive</hw>. <ety>[Cf. Sp. <ets>aceituna de la Reina</ets>
olive of the Queen.]</ety> <fld>(Olive Trade)</fld> <def>Properly, a
kind of superior olive grown in the region of Seville, Spain. It is
large size and oblong shape with a small but long pit; it is cured when
green, keeps well, and has a delicate flavor. Loosely, any olive of
similar character.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

